ATTRIBUTION REQUIREMENTS (CPAL 1.0 - Exhibit B)
================================================================================

When using this software, you must display attribution in the Dashboard UI.

ACCEPTABLE ATTRIBUTION OPTIONS (choose one):

  Option 1: Logo with link
    - Display the OpenShort.link logo (https://openshort.link/logo.png)
    - Link the logo to https://openshort.link
  
  Option 2: Text phrase with link
    - Display "Powered by OpenShort.link"
    - Link the text to https://openshort.link
  
  Option 3: Both logo and text
    - Display both logo and text phrase
    - Link to https://openshort.link

WHERE ATTRIBUTION MUST BE DISPLAYED:

  ✓ Dashboard UI (all pages accessible via /dashboard/*)
  ✓ Login and setup pages
  ✓ Any "About" or "Credits" sections
  ✓ Footer of all dashboard pages

WHERE ATTRIBUTION IS NOT REQUIRED:

  ✗ Redirect responses (/go/*, /r/*, or other redirect routes)
  ✗ API JSON responses
  ✗ HTTP headers or other non-UI outputs

The attribution must be displayed in a manner reasonably calculated to make 
it visible to users. For the exact legal requirements, see the LICENSE file, 
Section 14 and Exhibit B.

